OL,3,CMeet the bookbinder with a key role in
OL,4,Cthe Booker Prize ceremony
OL,6,FA book binder from Wiltshire has spent
OL,7,Faround 150 hours designing and binding
OL,8,Fa unique copy of one of the novels
OL,9,Fshortlisted for this year's Booker
OL,10,FPrize.
OL,12,FKate Holland, from Corsley, is a
OL,13,Fmember of the Designer Bookbinders
OL,14,FFellows. She is recognised as having
OL,15,Fachieved the highest standards of
OL,16,Fbookbinding in both technique and
OL,17,Fdesign.
OL,19,FEvery year, the society is asked to
OL,20,Fcreate a uniquely bound edition for
OL,21,Feach one of the Booker Prize Shortlist.
