OL,3,CMeet the bookbinder with a key role in
OL,4,Cthe Booker Prize ceremony
OL,6,F"I went through the book and I chose
OL,7,Fall the words that expressed the slave
OL,8,Fexperience. So it was hungry, crazy,
OL,9,Flawless, troubled. All of these
OL,10,Femotive strong words - but underneath
OL,11,Fthose words, I've written hope and
OL,12,Ffreedom because that's what the
OL,13,Fcharacter Jim is aiming for."
OL,15,FThe typeface Kate used for the book's
OL,16,Ftitle is the same typeface that would
OL,17,Fhave been used for advertisements for
OL,18,Fslaves for sale. She also used slave
OL,19,Fadvertisements, wood engravings and a
OL,20,Fmap of the Mississippi River in her
OL,21,Fdesign.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
