OL,3,CMeet the bookbinder with a key role in
OL,4,Cthe Booker Prize ceremony
OL,6,F"It's a brilliant job because you get
OL,7,Fto go really in-depth into a subject
OL,8,Fyou know nothing about.
OL,10,F"Every element in here is bound by my
OL,11,Fown hands. I then have to hand it over
OL,12,Fto the author, who obviously has no
OL,13,Fconcept of what the design is like or
OL,14,Fhow I've responded to the text.
OL,16,F"Hopefully he will like it - last time
OL,17,Fhe was very kind and enthusiastic, so
OL,18,Fwe'll see how it goes down."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
